Happy 6th Birthday to you my son, Eastan. 🎂

Every year I have encompassed your life in pictures and shared them on your birthday. I also share what you mean to me and share some inspirational post. 

This year, I’m sharing you. Some of the last year of your life in pictures and what you’ve been up to this year. Simply, you have done so much it’s hard to share all at once lol 

This year of your life… 

You learned so much. You grew and developed into the little man you are today. 

From the start of the year you took trips, had family and friends visit and had so much fun. You went to Dallas numerous times, Orlando, Oregon, New Mexico and many other places. 

You went to birthday parties, celebrated many times for many events with your fiends all the while making many new ones. 

You cut your hair!

You Graduated from Ivy Brook Academy and then did summer camp. You’re now almost half way through your Kindergarten year at Cooper Central. 

You left gymnastics after so many years and traded it for Karate. Ready to test for you yellow belt already!

You played your first year of football and loved it. You learned and got better through each game and practice. You also lost 4 mouth pieces alone the way lol

You’re now poised to play baseball next, something  you’re very excited about. 

Your girlfriend is still Cora, although the entire country separates you. All other girls are ”gross”. I’m curious to see how long this lasts lol. You sure are dedicated and loyal, but you’re exactly that to all those you love and who you call your friend. 

You swam, danced, you’ve eaten good foods, seen a lot of movies, played alot of games. 

You’ve trick or treated, laughed alot and asked a million questions about life and all around you in between. 

You got your first stitches and handled it like a champ. 

You’ve played with, taught and loved on your brother and have built upon a special bond you’ll carry through life. 

You’ve gotten perfect grades and share things with me I didn’t learn until years ahead of where you are now. You amaze me every day. 

You’re kind, loving, give all you have to people and projects, smart, giving and a delight to be around. 

CONT. 👇
Focused… 😐

Merry Christmas 🎁

A bit of a different holiday note today… 

Often people will ask me how my relationship works with my ex. How do we coparent etc. When you put the things and the person that matters most and at the forefront of your decisions, communicate well, listen, and treat one another with respect, things work well.

You lose some things in a divorce, but if you play your cards right so to speak and don’t let pettiness, insecurities, anger or any other negative attributes take hold, you then can in fact gain back so much more. 

Things can be good enough to share a special day like today. Void of awkwardness and hostility. Celebrating, talking, laughing, eating, creating and sharing new memories and showing equal support to the little person that you share, while equally supporting the people in each others lives that you don’t. 

Today meant a lot to my son for many reasons. And for those reasons he will always be worth it for me, her and everyone else we separately have as a part of our lives. 

A very Merry Christmas to you and a Happy upcoming New Year. 

Today was a good day… a really good day and I hope you experienced the same.
Let it snow ❄️
That time of the year again
🍯🧸 He Thick!

My Team is better than…

They were yesterday…. 

And that’s all anyone can ask or expect of anyone or themselves. 

You might have thought I was gonna say “better than XYZ” *insert person/team/entity etc*. That was intentional btw, but we don’t work that way. You don’t have to belittle others to be great. You’re just as great without that. 

We are always on a mission to be our own best selves and collectively better together. There is nothing wrong with being competitive, recognizing or sharing success or ability. Winning inspires others to find and recognize their own greatness. I just don’t think you have to put anyone down in the process.

These ladies pushed through a tough leg and glute workout day at Gym Culture with me.

There was some laying on the turf, longer breaks and alot of pushing themselves mentally… but they never quit, never complained and all finished a tough workout. All while cheering and encouraging one another on. 

That’s the type of “Culture” I want to be a part of and hopefully instill in those im luckily enough to work with or call friends. 

I hope everyone finds a way to win in their own way and in things they deem important. Today was a day of winning for some of those close to me and I’m proud of them for it.

*I am currently accepting online training clients and one in person client*

I’m a little late to the party, but I wanted to share that my son Eastan is a brother for the second time. Dallas was born last week. 

Eastan will spend his life with Dallas and his brother Callan. They’ll be confidants, brothers and best friends. They’ll laugh together, they’ll cry, they’ll fight, they’ll make up and be there for each others brightest and darkest days. They’ll grow together, learn together…. And be their best self because they have one another. 

A built in best friend, now X 2.

He may not be mine…. But he’s his…. (Eastan’s) and I’ll forever be grateful for those in his life that will be there when I’m not. That will encourage him to be all that he can be, help him discover his greatness, challenge him, teach him things I won’t, show him grace and kindness and love him unconditionally like I do. 

I guess though at this point, it may be up to me to give him a sister? 🤔 lol

Congrats to his mom and Bryan- and my very best to you and your growing family.

Did you know the average age for kids to tie their shoes is 6, but some aren’t comfortable until the age of 8?

Eastan is 6 and has always had velcro or pull on shoes. Today he told me he wanted to learn to tie his own shoes. So we practiced. I consider this his first time doing it himself (even though I got it started for him) because this is when HE recognized he could do it on his own. 

You can see him kinda well up a bit as he got a little emotional. He told me “Dad, these tears are of joy”. 

After this, he practiced and got the whole thing down all by himself. I’m Super proud of him for him for not only doing it, but at his own pace when he was ready.

We have our Gym Culture grand opening April 22nd here in Lubbock Texas. 

A special friend is going to come join the festivities to celebrate and support our opening 🎉

If you’ve ever met Jay you know he’s as world class of a person as he was a bodybuilder and is as a businessman. 

This isn’t a meet and greet, but Jay will be interacting with the attendees as he does at any event he attends. 

We look forward to seeing all of you who can join in the fun to help us celebrate. 🥳

Yesterday was a good day. Gym Culture’s grand opening and ribbon cutting was a success. 

Thank you to everyone for your support. It means a lot and this project wouldn’t be what it is without you. This also applies to my partners (wouldn’t be here without them) and all our amazing staff. 

I had some close friends come out to support me that I don’t get to see all that often, but when I do… I always walk away feeling better for being in their presence. (Brandon,Todd,Neil,Drew,) I’m thankful they made it. But, I also had friends and family from across the country checking in and sending their well wishes and sending their support too… they’ve been doing so since this project first started. 

Thank you. 

I’d like to give a BIG thank you to @jaycutler  I’ve been blessed to get the opportunity to get to know him over the past few years and can say with 100% certainty that he’s truly an amazing individual.  He’s a friend, story teller, businessman, dog dad and lover of animals, motivator, entrepreneur, hard worker and as smart as they come, but with a kindness and willingness to share and help others that’s often unmatched. Oh yea, and he’s one of the greatest bodybuilders of all time ( in case you didn’t know lol) but as I shared above, a great person too, first and foremost. 

I watched him this past weekend interact with others, stay present and engaged, share advice, but also ask a ton of questions showing interest in those that were so excited to meet him. It’s those attributes that makes people truly feel special. All while taking a photo with someone new what felt like every 5 seconds for the entirety of the event, with no less enthusiasm from when he started. 

If you haven’t met Jay, he’s a special dude. There’s no way around it. And I’m proud to call him a friend and thankful he took the time to come share.. well… HIMSELF with our community. 

Thank you Jay 💪

Community Inspired….People Driven is our motto 

We are inspired by all of you as we are everyday and we are driven by you to continue to grow and be the best us we can for all of you.

Thank you for making this dream a reality. 

Much more to come 💪

We have a first grader (almost). Instead of a graduation, Eastan’s class had an award day. 

It’s truly insane how fast this year has gone, how much he’s learned, grown (mentally and physically) and I couldn’t be more proud.

I met Mike Servin online over 4 years ago… this came after seeing a viral video of him preaching and dancing on stage. We hit it off right away and have remained friends since. 

If you don’t know Mike, he’s an ex gang member who’s over come a lot. He’s out there sharing the word of God and doing it his way, unapologetically himself. 

Mike made a post this week and I realized he was in town, so after 4 years of chatting, I had to reach out and invite him to the gym. Of which he obliged. 

Over the years Mike has reached out to pray for me, send words of encouragement and just check in to see how life is going and if I’m good. 

Whether you’re a believer or not, believe in God, positive energy, the Universe etc. it’s hard to deny Mike’s infectious energy and positive attitude. Im thankful he came by today to share his energy with all of us. 

When someone takes the time to pray for you, with you, share their energy with you, a kind word or speak positivity into your life, speak positively about you to others or offer an ear to listen means a lot to me and ill always be appreciative of those who do so, for me or for others.

I’ve never been the father of a 6 year old. Nor will I be a 7 year old and beyond. I’ll be growing, developing, evolving and adapting like just like you to the world around us and to you. I’ll learn as we go and I’ll learn to adapt to all life’s changes that change you along the way. 

I’ll always try be what you need. I’ll always try to be patient, kind and always be open to you. I’ll listen and be understanding. Ill teach you right from wrong, but I’ll also expose you to the world and let you decide what you want to do within it. I’ll be someone you can look up to and always be a safe place for you to come to for absolutely any and all things. 

I’ll walk your path with you as long as I’m able. I’ll try to guide you and assure you that your footing is stable and be the stability you need to keep moving forward. 

I’ll love you always and forever and there won’t be a day that I’m not grateful I’m your dad. #fathersday #dad
Happy Independence Day 🇺🇸🧨

We got away for the weekend…I got some work done and got to spend some time celebrating some recent life events with this one. 

Looking forward to the next chapters of life to come.

1st grader! 📚

Eastan had his open house today to meet his new teacher, see his classroom, pick a locker and sign up for various events etc. 

I can’t believe we have a 1st grader. 💙

1st Grade! 📚

This could be the first day of college or any year in between and I’d be just as proud as I am today. Every year is a step to something more. Learning, developing and growing into the man he will be. 💙

We had an awesome event at Gym Culture this past weekend and for a good cause. 

So many to thank and much to be thankful for. 

As a community we are capable of great things when we come together and I hope the Lubbock Fit Block Party showed that. We are better together and can move mountains as one as opposed to on our own. Although I think Phil Heath singularly could move one 🏔️ lol 

Written on our gym wall it says “Community Inspired, People Driven” 
We are inspired by others, we want to grow within our community and have other grow right along side us. We want to help others become their best selves and become our best in the process. 

We have many events ahead, more memories to make and good causes to support and lend our time and effort to. 

Next year…. This event will return. So stay tuned. But, before then we will have our 1 year anniversary party up next. Who should we bring as a “special guest” ? 👇

Thank you again to everyone who came, saw, participated, lent their stardom to our event for the day and made this 1st event a success. You are appreciated.

A BIG thank you to @philheath 

I want to extend my heartfelt gratitude for your presence at our event. Your willingness to share your knowledge, expertise, and dedication to excellence with our community left a profound impact. Your achievements and who you are as a man are an inspiration to us all.

Thank you for taking the time to engage with our community, and for being such an incredible source of motivation. Your contribution was invaluable, and we are truly honored to have had you with us. 

Continue to lead and know you matter and make a difference.

That’s a wrap 🎬

I’ve been a fan of cinema my whole life. I love movies and respect the process of making them. I never saw myself as an actor, but am blessed to know many and have been able to witness the process of making movies up close over the years. Never to be a part of one until now. 

I met @kellanlutz 10 years ago and we’ve remained friends since. Kellan is one if the best people I know and someone I have enjoyed watching over the years as they’ve gone from one project to another, but more so watching him transition in life. From a single guy when we met so many years ago to a husband and father, good one at that. Just a good human who treats everyone around him with respect, shows interest in those he meets and caters to those around him and makes them feel important and special. 

Following as his roles have changed as he’s aged and grown and what that process looks for him, what interests him now and the importance to continue to be present for his family. All while he works hard ( often away)  and takes on roles that he has an interest in that will allow him to available to those he cares about. 

I could go on and on about him, but in the end he’s a good friend. Kellan knew I’d always wanted to be in the background of a film, just once to be a part of the process just once. So, he made that happen. He got me into his most recent film and when I asked if Flavia could be on set, he went one further and got her a role right beside me. 

It was a blast to be a part of and awesome to share these moments with him and with her. I’m thankful for the opportunity and truly appreciative again for my friend- so again, thank you Kellan ( you’re still my favorite vampire lol). 

Lastly… now that I’ve done this and had so much fun, @kaiwilymanm the only other thing I have left is to find an extra spot and do one with you too 🎬 

I give this experience 5 stars… would do again. ⭐️

We had a great time last night with our friends here in Texas. We wanted to celebrate friendships we have here and spend some time with those who have become our local family.

Thank you to everyone who attended and spent your time with us. Thank you to our hosts for taking great care of us and our guests. And thank you to our great caterer for going above and beyond with your food and service. 

Next up…. 

June 22nd 2024 in South Dakota. 💍

*that last pic tho.. I got that pose down lol*

The October 30th episode of The Price is Right.

We were in LA for another TV project and a producer gave me VIP tickets to The Price is Right. So how could we not go? 

Sadly Bob Barker, who’s from South Dakota and being from there you grow up knowing that, passed away two days prior. So we were the first show to tape after his passing. They were filming a memorial show later that day. 

The whole process was awesome and it was truly a great time. Drew was really nice and accommodating and shared some stories and jokes while on breaks. The announcer teased Flavia and I numerous times. 

It took a few hours to check in, security, contracts, and interviews pre show, but again all fun. 

They specifically chose us and took us to the front row, but we didn’t make it “on” the show. Which is ok as it was fun to watch, give high fives to the winners, and play along form our seats. 

I would definitely do it again and plan to sometime in the future. 

My shirt said “ I’ve waited my whole life to spin the wheel”. One day, hopefully I will 💪

Happy 7th Birthday, Eastan! 🎂♥️

On this special day, I want you to know how truly amazing you are. You possess a heart full of kindness and a spirit overflowing with courage. Your imagination takes you on the most incredible adventures, and your athletic abilities show your strength and determination.

You are a light in this world, Eastan. Your intelligence and caring nature make you a  positive example to those around you. Remember, every challenge you face is an opportunity to learn and grow even stronger.

As you celebrate your 7th birthday, know that you've already made the world a brighter place just by being you. You have a unique gift for bringing joy and love into the lives of those you meet.

Keep exploring, keep dreaming, and keep being the wonderful person you are. The path ahead of you is filled with endless possibilities, and I am excited to see all the great things you will do.

You're not just my son; you're my hero and my inspiration. Your journey is a remarkable one, and I'm honored to be by your side every step of the way. Happy Birthday, and here's to many more adventures together!

With all my love…. Dad
